Document Steps to compile, build and run the project

** First you need to Download and install Node.js from 'https://nodejs.org/en/' if you don't have it on your system.

** Install and create database as explained in 'Build and create database.txt' file.

** Clone or download the project on your computer from 'https://github.com/kumarkrishna190/furlenco'

** Open your terminal ds into furlenco-blog-api and hit npm start, this will start the server.

** Open another terminal ds into furlenco-blog folder and hit npm start and that's it you will get your app running in browser.




** Steps to build for deployment

just hit npm run build in the project folder

This will builds the app for production to the build folder.
It correctly bundles React in production mode and optimizes the build for the best performance.


Your app is ready to be deployed!
